
[1]remunerate

   REMU'NERATE, v.t. [L. remunero; re and munero, from munus, a gift.]

   to reward; to recompense; to requite; in a good sense; to pay an
   equivalent to for any service, loss, expense or other sacrifice; as, to
   remunerate the troops of an army for their services and sufferings; to
   remunerate men for labor. the pious usfferer in this life will be
   remunerated in the life to come.
